  "prompt": "Can an IAS officer create a secret agency within the district?",
  "response": "An Indian Administrative Service (IAS) officer does not have the authority to create a secret agency within a district. IAS officers operate within the framework of the Constitution of India and the rules and regulations set by the government. Their functions and powers are defined by various laws and administrative procedures. Creating a secret agency would require authorization from higher governmental authorities and would need to follow legal and procedural guidelines.\n\nAny such initiative would typically involve significant oversight and require approval from relevant departments, such as the Ministry of Home Affairs or other security and intelligence agencies. Unauthorized creation of a secret agency could lead to legal ramifications and disciplinary actions against the officer involved.",
